  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Cooperation Fund (LCF) in Belize</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Maya people in southern Belize live in a region characterized as one of the few primary tropical rainforests in the country.  The project works in this region aiming to contribute to the safeguarding of the remaining rainforest and to return the responsibility for forest management back to the Mays living in the area. A practical aim is to strengthen two community-based forest management enterprises in Q&#xE2;&#x80;&#x99;eqchi&#xE2;&#x80;&#x99; Maya communities in the Toledo District through building local administrative capacity and improving the quality of production and storage capacity of sustainable timber.  A storage/ drying shed will be built for two community enterprises and monthly site visits will be conducted to the communities to review their financial reports and to ensure compliance with the forest management plan. The beneficiaries of the project will be some 450 people living in the two villages</narrative>
  </description>
